sql:
SELECT ATANH(AVG(value))
FROM results
WHERE algorithm_id = 1 AND config_id = 0;

SELECT version_name 
FROM problem_size_versions 
WHERE problem_size_id = 1;

SELECT problem_size_id, problem_size
FROM problem_sizes
WHERE problem_size > 10;

SELECT algorithm_name 
FROM algorithms 
WHERE created_by = 1 AND created_at > '2022-12-31';

SELECT a.algorithm_name, av.version_name
FROM algorithms a
INNER JOIN algorithm_versions av ON a.algorithm_id = av.algorithm_id;

SELECT problem_size_id, problem_size
FROM problem_sizes
WHERE problem_size > (SELECT AVG(problem_size) FROM problem_sizes);

external_knowledge:
- 'Analysts' refers to users whose role is specifically marked as 'analyst'.;
- 'Downloaded algorithms' implies that the analyst has an access log record with 'download' as the access type. ;
- 'Performance times' refer to the maximum values of the performance metrics measured for the algorithms on specific problem sizes. ;
- 'Top performance times' means the highest values of these performance metrics are considered as the best or most notable performance times, depending on the context. In this case, it's the maximum execution time.

sql:
SELECT problem_size_id, COUNT(*) AS total_versions
FROM problem_size_versions
GROUP BY problem_size_id;
